<h1> Hybrid Method</h1>

<h3>
    The Hybrid Method is in my opinion the best option.  In the Hybrid method, you take the strategy from the Snowball method and add it to the Avalanche strategy.  First organize the debts interest rates
    from greatest to smallest, just like in the Avalanche method.  Attack this debt until it is gone, and then roll that payment amount into attacking the next hightest interest rate debt.
    Remember you are still responsible to make the minimum payments on each of the other debts along the way.
</h3>


<h3>
    Let's say for example you have three debts to pay, Student Loan at $23,674 with an interest rate of 4.27%, Medical Bill at $12,813 with an interest rate of 4.9%, and
    Car Loan at $19,985 with an interest rate of 5%.  Using the Hybrid method the first thing you would do is to organize the debt interest rate amounts from greatest to least.
</h3>



