    </table>




<h3>
    Like in the Avalanche method, the Car Loan still has the greatest overall interest rate.  Your goal is to get rid of that debt as soon as possible.  The higher interst rate
    is costing you more money.  While making the minimum payments on the Medical Bill and the Student Loan, you will also make EXTRA payments on the Car Loan.  Your extra payment
    may only be $5 over the minimum amount, that's ok.  Pay as much as you can in extra based on your income.  Once the Car Loan is paid off, roll the $377.14 (plus your extra 
    payment) into a new extra payment on the Medical Bill (the next highest interest rate debt).
</h3>

<h3>
    The Hybrid methood combines the best from both strategies to make a super charged strategy.  The results are experienced much faster.  Selecting to pay off the higher interest rate first
    will save money on interest, (Avalanche method).  Plus adding the extra payment to the next highest interest rate debt, (Snowball method), will add speed to the payoff!  This by far is the
    superior method.
</h3>

